docs.abstract: A handful of rogue electoral votes, if allowed, could tip the next presidential election.
docs.snippet: A handful of rogue electoral votes, if allowed, could tip the next presidential election.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Supreme Court agreed Friday to decide whether members of the Electoral College may cast their votes for presidential candidates other than the ones they had pledged to support.

headline.main: Supreme Court to Hear Timely Case on Electoral College Voters
headline.print_headline: Justices Take Case on ‘Faithless Electors’ in the Electoral College

docs.abstract: Successful in raising small contributions online and six-figure ones from wealthy donors, the campaign now wants to tap into supporters who can “bundle” contributions from friends and business associates.
docs.snippet: Successful in raising small contributions online and six-figure ones from wealthy donors, the campaign now wants to tap into supporters who can “bundle” contributions from friends and business associates.
docs.lead_paragraph: President Trump’s re-election campaign plans to step up its efforts to capitalize on so-called bundlers, supporters who can raise money from friends and business associates in increments up to $2,800, the legal limit for a level of giving that has lagged in the campaign despite a far more sophisticated fund-raising operation than existed in 2016.

headline.main: Trump Campaign Plans Greater Focus on ‘Bundlers’
headline.print_headline: Trump Aides Shifting Focus To Donations By ‘Bundlers’

docs.abstract: Ken Starr and a third lawyer named to the team, Robert Ray, were independent counsels who investigated President Bill Clinton.
docs.snippet: Ken Starr and a third lawyer named to the team, Robert Ray, were independent counsels who investigated President Bill Clinton.
docs.lead_paragraph: President Trump enlisted the former independent counsel Ken Starr and the celebrity lawyer Alan Dershowitz to join his defense team on Friday, turning to two veterans of politically charged legal cases to secure his acquittal in the Senate impeachment trial that gets underway in earnest next week.

headline.main: Trump Legal Team Adds Starr and Dershowitz for Senate Trial
headline.print_headline: President Giving  His Defense Team A Celebrity Cast

docs.abstract: The Treasury Department plans roll out 20-year bonds this year for the first time since 1986.
docs.snippet: The Treasury Department plans roll out 20-year bonds this year for the first time since 1986.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — With years of trillion-dollar deficits ahead, the Treasury Department says it will soon begin issuing 20-year bonds in an effort to generate investor interest in government debt.

headline.main: With Deficit Swelling, U.S. Will Issue New Class of Bonds
headline.print_headline: U.S. Is Issuing 20-Year Bonds To Pay Down Swelling Deficit

docs.abstract: President Trump cited Maj. Gen. Qassim Suleimani’s “horrible past” as possibly reason enough for the drone strike that killed him.
docs.snippet: President Trump cited Maj. Gen. Qassim Suleimani’s “horrible past” as possibly reason enough for the drone strike that killed him.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — In the 10 days since it carried out the drone strike that killed Maj. Gen. Qassim Suleimani, the Trump administration has been struggling to draft an after-the-fact narrative to justify it. On Monday, President Trump put an end to that hash of explanations. “It doesn’t really matter,” he tweeted, “because of his horrible past.”

headline.main: A Narrative Collapses as Trump Tweets: ‘It Doesn’t Really Matter’
headline.print_headline: Trump Stops Trying to Explain Suleimani Killing

docs.abstract: An inquiry into years-old disclosures of classified information is highly unusual and leaves law enforcement officials open to accusations of politicizing their work.
docs.snippet: An inquiry into years-old disclosures of classified information is highly unusual and leaves law enforcement officials open to accusations of politicizing their work.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Federal prosecutors in Washington are investigating a years-old leak of classified information about a Russian intelligence document, and they appear to be focusing on whether the former F.B.I. director James B. Comey illegally provided details to reporters, according to people familiar with the inquiry.

headline.main: Justice Dept. Investigating Years-Old Leaks and Appears Focused on Comey
headline.print_headline: Inquiry in Leak May Put Focus Back on Comey

docs.abstract: The president said in Davos, Switzerland, that he was planning to add more countries to an executive order barring people from predominantly Muslim countries.
docs.snippet: The president said in Davos, Switzerland, that he was planning to add more countries to an executive order barring people from predominantly Muslim countries.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration plans to introduce an updated version of a long-disputed travel ban enacted shortly after President Trump’s inauguration in 2017, expanding the list to include countries the White House has suggested have fallen out of compliance with United States security measures.

headline.main: Trump Considering an Expansion of His 2017 Travel Ban
headline.print_headline: President Plans to Expand Number of Countries Under 2017 Travel Ban
